race.comment: CARPE ASTRA (11) has shown promising signs in her first two outings and looks ready to peak now. She'll be handy in the run again and, with natural improvement, should take plenty of holding out. ELEGANT LILLY (12) looked poised to go on with the job when resuming at Oakbank but just lacked that final bit of fitness late. She'll be much better for the run and is capable of going one better here. MISS SLIPSTREAM (10) returns from a long break and may need the run but did show plenty of positive signs in her debut prep. Market support will be a good guide. MISS BOOM (9) also returns and has been tuned up for this with two jumpout wins. Tootell sticks and she's worth keeping safe.
